    <stitle>VT 275 Engine Service Manual - Fuel System - Removal and Disassembly - Secondary Fuel Filter</stitle>
    <svcman/>
    <svcproc id="e30013" svcproctype="replace" graphiccount="5">
        <title>Secondary Fuel Filter</title>
        <figure id="f3001306" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figJ11/J11004.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px" box="no"/>
            <caption>Secondary fuel filtration tubing</caption>
            <calloutgroup>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Fuel return (to tank)</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Fuel supply (from tank)</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Diagnostic port plug, M12</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Fuel supply tube to left cylinder head</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Fuel supply tube to right cylinder head</callout1>
            </calloutgroup>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Drain the fuel filter housing by placing a suitable container beneath the fuel diagnostic
                port plug. Remove plug, then crack open fuel filter cap to allow air into filter housing. Place plug
                back into port when filter housing is empty.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove all tube connections attached to fuel filter assembly as follows:</para>
            <figure id="f3001307" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figj11/J11006.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"/>
                <caption>Fuel supply tube and fitting gaskets</caption>
            </figure>
            <step2>
                <para count="1">Remove fuel filter banjo bolt and discard copper washers.</para>
                <figure id="f3001308" figsize="col-wide">
                    <graphic filename="../figj11/J11019.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"/>
                    <caption>Fuel return tube fitting</caption>
                </figure>
            </step2>
            <step2>
                <para count="1">Using backup wrenches, disconnect fuel return tube fitting and discard O-rings.</para>
            </step2>
            <step2>
                <para count="1">Using backup wrenches, disconnect left and right cylinder head fuel tubing and discard
                    O-rings.
                </para>
            </step2>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Using the Cap Kit (all), cap all open ports on the secondary fuel filter housing. See
                <hotlnk document="eges3001_279.xml" xrefid="E30013C" appearance="hottext">Special Service Tools</hotlnk>
                .
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove secondary fuel filter assembly mounting screws (M6 x 25) for further disassembly and
                inspection.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove secondary fuel filter assembly.</para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f3001309" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figj11/j11060.cgm" type="cgm" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"/>
            <caption>Pressure regulator poppet assembly</caption>
            <calloutgroup>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Oil filter assembly</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Fuel filter assembly</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Screw, M6 x 25 (3)</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Pressure regulator cover gasket</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Viton O-ring, size #115</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Poppet gasket seal</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Brass poppet</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Pressure regulator valve spring</callout1>
            </calloutgroup>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Removing the filter assembly exposes the pressure regulator poppet components. Remove these
                parts for later inspection.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f3001310" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figj11/j11061.cgm" type="cgm" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"/>
            <caption>Fuel filter assembly</caption>
            <calloutgroup>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Fuel filter cap</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">O-ring seal</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Fuel filter element</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Fuel return tube assembly</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Screw, 8/32 x 3/8 in (2)</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Viton O-ring, size #112</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Fuel filter housing</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Fuel return fitting, M16</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Left and right cylinder head fuel tube assembly fitting, M12 (2)</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Diagnostic pressure test port plug, M12</callout1>
            </calloutgroup>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Loosen fuel filter cap and discard O-ring seal.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Before removing filter, depress filter to verify spring loaded fuel return tube is free.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Lift out secondary fuel filter element and discard.</para>
        </step1>
